<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="182" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[783,1375,308,727]" lastBlockId="53.[169,1375,738,1161]" pageId="53" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[783,894,541,570]" pageId="53" pageNumber="182">Habitat.</emphasis>
Primary evergreen pre-montane forest with relatively open canopy, wet and rocky soil, some epiphytes and lianas, abundant leaf litter, abundant moss on tree trunks, roots, and rocks, and ferns and orchids, at elevations of 800-1500 m (based on several of five known capture localities).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
